   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Next-Generation Vision Transformer for Particle Physics Detector Images\n",
    "\n",
    "**Multi-Task Learning: Mass Regression + Quark–Gluon Classification**\n",
    "\n",
    "Combining **XCiT Cross-Covariance Attention**, **L2ViT Local Concentration Modules**, and **Linear Attention** for CMS End-to-End Deep Learning.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Author:** Rahul Gupta  \n",
    "**Affiliation:** ML4SCI / CMS Experiment, CERN  \n",
    "**Context:** GSoC Prototype — Vision Transformers for End-to-End Particle Reconstruction  \n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## SECTION 1 — Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "### Particle Physics Detector Images\n",
    "\n",
    "The CMS detector at the Large Hadron Collider (LHC) records particle collisions as multi-channel images. Each \"jet image\" is a 125×125 pixel map from three sub-detector systems:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Channel | Sub-Detector | What It Measures |\n",
    "|---------|-------------|------------------|\n",
    "| 0 | **Tracker** | Charged particle tracks (momentum) |\n",
    "| 1 | **ECAL** | Electromagnetic calorimeter (electron/photon energy) |\n",
    "| 2 | **HCAL** | Hadronic calorimeter (hadron energy) |\n",
    "\n",
    "Each pixel represents energy deposited in an (ieta, iphi) bin of the detector. The input tensor shape is **(batch_size, 3, 125, 125)**.\n",
    "\n",
    "This project is a fork of the **ML4SCI/E2E** repository, which contains prior GSoC implementations:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Anis Ismail (GSoC 2021)** — ResNet-15 for mass regression using MAE loss, Parquet data loading with channel scaling  \n",
    "  *(Reference: `E2E_Regression_Anis_Ismail/models.py`, `data_utils.py`, `train_utils.py`)*\n",
    "- **Diptarko Choudhury (GSoC 2022)** — Swin Transformer, CoAtNet, Hybrid EffSwin for classification (ROC-AUC: 81.46 on QG, 98.77 on Top)  \n",
    "  *(Reference: `E2E_Visual_Image_Transformer_Diptarko_Choudhury/`)*\n",
    "- **Ka Wa Ho** — Custom Swin Transformer with DDP multi-GPU, WandB, AMP training  \n",
    "  *(Reference: `E2E_Visual_Image_Transformer_Ka_Wa_Ho/run_train_test_parallel.py`)*\n",
    "\n",
    "### End-to-End Deep Learning\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of hand-engineered features, we feed raw detector images directly into a deep neural network. The E2E pipeline from the repository reads Parquet files via PyArrow, applies per-channel scaling (Tracker: ×0.02, ECAL: ×0.2, HCAL: ×1.0), zero-suppression, and high-value clipping.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why Standard Self-Attention O(N²) Is Problematic\n",
    "\n",
    "A 125×125 image with patch_size=5 produces N=625 tokens. Standard self-attention computes a full N×N matrix, which is **O(N²·d)** — expensive for high-resolution detector images.\n",
    "\n",
    "### How XCiT Achieves O(N) via Channel Attention\n",
    "\n",
    "XCiT (Cross-Covariance Image Transformer) transposes the attention problem: instead of computing **token×token** attention (N×N), it computes **channel×channel** attention (d×d). Since d << N, this is **O(N·d²)** ≈ O(N). Crucially, Q and K are **L2-normalized** before the dot product for training stability.\n",
    "\n",
    "### How L2ViT Introduces Local Context\n",
    "\n",
    "Linear/channel-wise attention can lose spatial locality. L2ViT introduces a **Local Concentration Module (LCM)** — a 3×3 depth-wise convolution inside the attention path — to inject local spatial inductive bias and prevent the \"distribution concentration\" problem.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Our Architecture: NextGen-ViT\n",
    "\n",
    "We unify all of the above:\n",
    "1. **Convolutional patch embedding** (from CoAtNet / Hybrid EffSwin ideas)\n",
    "2. **XCiT cross-covariance attention** with L2-normalized Q,K\n",
    "3. **L2ViT local concentration module** (depth-wise convolution)\n",
    "4. **Conditional positional encoding** (depth-wise conv, resolution-agnostic)\n",
    "5. **Dual-head output**: classification (Quark vs Gluon) + regression (mass)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## SECTION 2 — Environment Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
